Class AppUserFactory<AU extends AppUser>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.DataObjectFactory<AU>
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.session.AppUserFactory<AU>
  • Type Parameters:
    AU - type of AppUser
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, ContextCached, FormCreatorProducer, FormUpdateProducer<AU>, FilterMatcher<AU>, TypeConverter<AU,java.lang.Number>, Selector<DataObjectItemInput<AU>>, Owner, IndexedProducer<AU>, NameFinder<AU>, ParseFactory<AU>, SummaryContributer<AU>, RegisterTrigger<AU>, RequiredPageProvider<AU>, Tagged, Targetted<AU>

    public class AppUserFactory<AU extends AppUser>
extends DataObjectFactory<AU>
implements RequiredPageProvider<AU>, NameFinder<AU>, RegisterTrigger<AU>, SummaryContributer<AU>
    A Factory for creating AppUser objects that represent users of the system. If the bootstrap.admin Feature is set then the first user in the system will automatically be given the ADMIN role (or the role specified in the bootstrap-role property is this is set). The role is added when the table for this factory is created not when the user is added.
    Author:
    spb
